5 grams Coriander
1 sachet(s) Soy Sauce
1 unit(s) Lime
1 sachet(s) Vegetable Stock
150 grams Jasmine Rice
1 unit(s) Onion
1 sachet(s) Sweet Chilli Sauce
1 unit(s) Carrot
75 grams Broccolini
1 sachet(s) Garlic, Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
250 grams Irish Beef Strips
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil
to taste Water

Pour 300ml cold salted water (double for 4p) into a medium pot with a tight-fitting lid.
Stir in the rice and bring to the boil.
Lower the heat to medium, cover with the lid and cook for 12 mins.
Once cooked, remove the pot from the heat.
Keep covered for another 12 mins or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, quarter the lime.
Roughly chop the coriander (stalks and all).
Trim the carrot and halve widthways. Chop lengthways into ½ cm thick batons.
Halve, peel and thinly slice the onion.

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once hot, fry the beef strips and lemongrass paste until the beef is browned, shifting as it colours, 2-3 mins. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging. Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.
Remove from the pan and set aside. Cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Once hot, add the carrot and fry for 4-5 mins.
Add the broccolini and onion to the pan.
Fry for another 3-4 mins.

Add the stock to the pan along with 25ml water (double for 4p).
Cover and cook until the veg is tender, 4-5 mins.
Remove the pan from the heat.
Stir through the beef strips, soy sauce, sweet chilli sauce and juice from half the lime wedges.

Fluff up the rice with a fork and divide between plates.
Serve the flavourful beef and veg alongside.
Garnish with chopped coriander and remaining lime wedges.